Are you ready to fall for the Villain?

“Play for me, Juliet…”

Those four words whispered in my ear again and again until I craved what I used to fear.
Such a simple demand from my captor—the man who stole me and refused to tell me why he wouldn’t let me go.

I was his.
He made me need him, just as much as he needed me.
I broke all the rules of the golden prison he put me in. 

During the day he ruled his dark, seedy world.
His subjects and me.

During the night—he bowed before my feet. 

Have you ever wondered what happened to the villains in all the fairy tales you read?
You’ll soon find out.

It all started when he kidnapped me and made me his pet.
And it all ended with me…

Calling him master.

This last month has truly been a crazy time emotionally and mentally for me. I always try to keep my social media a happy place and I don’t share much of my private life outside of making book content. 

As you guys know, my dad had surgery today and up until a few hours ago, we thought he was going to have a biopsy and pathology on legions they thought they saw, but we’re actually just inflammation 🙏🏼

You have no idea how had these last few weeks were for me. I didn’t tell anyone what was happening outside of my immediate family. I just couldn’t talk about it. It was too scary and real. Too many what if’s and questions I didn’t have the answers for. I think this is the scariest thing that’s happened to me in my adult life, as most of you know, my parents are my life. 

I never appreciated the expression, “They’re not here forever,” like I did this past month. When my sister called me this afternoon with the great news, I immediately broke down in my car from happiness. The relief I feel for the future doesn’t have words. I can’t express my gratitude toward the big man above. The fact that my dad is okay is truly the biggest gift of all. 

Being on Perfect Enemy deadline while this was happening saved my life. I was able to get lost in that in the moments I felt myself losing my mind. It helped so much to write out some of my feelings! 

Between deadline, vacation, bronchitis and my dad, I think my body just crashed! I’m happy to report that I’m feeling much better!

Life update: 

As you guys found out with my post yesterday about my dad, it has been a taxing month for me. I can’t tell you the relief I feel today knowing he’s going to be okay! Over the last couple weeks, I’ve been pulled in several different places and have managed to make it work and release Perfect Enemy. Which to be completely honest, saved me from having absolute meltdown with everything that was going on. 

My toxic trait is that I tend to bury myself in work when I have stressful and overwhelming things happening around me. It’s how I keep going and stay focused. Because of that, we have a lot of exciting thing happening in our @vipbookshop and Box of Alphas!

Now that I feel like I can breathe again, we also got some great news today! Our rental got approved and we will be moving back into a house on the 26th of the month. We found a property that actually has a boat slip that can fit Lost Boy, so now we will have our home and boat in the same place. 

We loved living boat life since Feb of 2022, but we’re ready for more space and the dogs are ready too. With the scare we had with my dad, it really put things into perspective for me. As some of you know, over the last few years we’ve lived on and off with my parents and we’ve been wanting to live with them again, so it’s perfect timing! 

I can’t wait to show you guys our new place for the next 2 years while we wait for the market to settle down to hopefully buy some land and build. Our ultimate goal is to build our forever home with a mother and father in law space for my parents. I was raised in a very traditional Hispanic home and I always knew I’d eventually be taking care of them which is something I want to do for for everything they’ve done for me. 

I’m super fortunate to be married to a man who loves them as much as I do and completely embraced my culture. He has no problem living together. My dad actually works for Bossman’s construction company as a manager for the last 13 years. 

They love him more than they love me 😂

I’m also thinking about new content! Of course decorate with me videos and maybe a cooking series with my mom that we can incorporate my books!

18 years later and we’re maybe moving back to the beach city where our relationship began 🥹

This is so unbelievably nostalgic for us and how we’ve truly come full circle in our life. The first 2 years of our relationship, Bossman lived in Apollo Beach. The first year, he rented a house with his sister and his then brother in law. The following year, they bought a house and we moved into my sisters garage. 

Yes, you read that correctly 😂

For a little over a year, we lived in a 2 car garage that Bossman turned into what he likes to still call a studio apartment 🤣

I was still living at home, but you know how it goes… I was basically staying with him every night and the fact that it was technically my sisters house, it was easier to get away with not coming home 😉

Although, I was 21 at the time, my parents didn’t care. I was still the like a little girl who went from my parents hands to Bossman’s ❤️

He always jokes that he got me when I was young 😏

The first picture is Bossman checking to make sure our boat will fit in the slip behind the house we want to rent. The dogs of course are supervising 🐶 

The second photo is us standing on the beach we had our second date on 😭 It’s a bike ride away from the property and dog friendly! 

Bossman always loved this beach town, I just never thought we’d be moving back there again and it has me all up in my feels 😩

Just need to confirm one more thing for the boat and we will know for sure if we’re moving in on the 26th!

This picture was right before I started writing my first book VIP almost 12 years ago. I began writing a day before my 27th birthday. I remember feeling so unfulfilled with my career path. I was in school getting my doctorate in Psychology. 

At the time, I was unbelievably passionate about reading. I was always enthusiastically telling Bossman about my books and I was a book a night reader.

One day after telling him about my dream that I had an affair with Alexander Starsgard. I felt so bad, but Bossman’s first words after I told him about my dream was “There’s your first storyline.” For the next year, he pushed me to write a book and since I was used to writing long as thesis papers he thought it’d be perfect for me 

Finally, I gave in and wrote my first words ever…

This isn’t a love story, but a story about love. 

I actually have tattooed down my forearm. I remember what it felt like to type out those words as if I just wrote them this morning. For the first time in my life, I felt like I found my calling. What I was put on earth to do. After eight months of writing, I released VIP not expecting a damn thing. 

Within a day of my release @the_real_totallybookedblog read and reviewed VIP. At the time, blogs ran the book world and they’re freaking HUGE. I couldn’t believe they read it and overnight, my book blew up.  I was able to drop out of school and quit my job. My family and husband fully supportive. 

I owe a lot to Jenny and Gitte and I’ll forever be grateful to them and I’ve told them several times! 

Tomorrow is my 39th birthday! I’ve been Bossman since I was 20 years old. He used to sneak me into bars and clubs with my sisters fake ID. Soon I’ll be with this man more than I’ve been by myself. There’s so many goals I want to accomplish this next year and some are already in the works. 

If I could go back and tell this girl anything it would be, you’re headed into the most amazing, emotional, rollercoaster of a career that will mean everything to you. 

The truth is, I don’t feel almost 39 years old and I think that’s the secret to happiness. Age is just a number and you can absolutely flip the page and start a new chapter of your life at any age.
